Using the above claim, we see that:
       \begin {align*}       \sum _{ i=1 }^{ k } p(e_{ i }) &\leq  \sum _{ i=1 }^{ k } \frac {c(S)}{k-i+1} \\       &= c(S) \sum _{ i=1 }^{ k } \frac {1}{i} \\       &= c(S) \cdot  \mathcal {H}_{ k }     \end {align*}    

  Therefore, summing over all values of \hat {y}  gives us:
       \begin {align*}       \sum _{ i=1 }^{ k } y_{ e_i } &= \sum _{ i=1 }^{ k } p(e_{ i })       \frac {1}{\mathcal {H}_{ n }} \\       &\leq  \sum _{ i=1 }^{ k } c(S) \frac {\mathcal {H}_{ k       }}{\mathcal {H}_{ n }} \\       &\leq  c(S)     \end {align*}    

  where \frac {\mathcal {H}_{ k }}{\mathcal {H}_{ n }} \leq  1 .
